
- First run ./install.sh - this will use zc.buildout to set up everything on
  Python side
  
- Install PostgreSQL using

  - $ sudo apt-get install postgresql (Ubuntu and friends)
  - zzZzzzZz (Mac)
  
- As a user postgres, do:

  - $ createuser --no-superuser --no-createdb --no-createrole zato1
  - $ createdb --owner=zato1 zato1
  - $ psql --dbname zato1 --command="ALTER ROLE zato1 WITH PASSWORD 'zato1'"
  
- Back to the normal user, do:

  - $ sudo service postgresql start
  
- Setting up a new environment using the 'zato quickstart' command

  - $ mkdir ~/tmp/zato1
  - $ cd ~/tmp/zato1
  - $ ~/projects/zato/code/bin/zato quickstart postgresql localhost 5432 zato1 zato1 localhost 5672 zato1